Data license — public/data/
============================

The generated data in this directory (kanji-3d.json and any other files
here) is a derivative work of the KANJIDIC2 dictionary file: the kanji
meanings (`m`) and on/kun readings (`on`/`kun`) are extracted directly from
KANJIDIC2, and the 3D coordinates (`x`/`y`/`z`), type (`t`) and cluster id
(`c`) are computed from those meanings.

KANJIDIC2 is the property of the Electronic Dictionary Research and
Development Group (EDRDG), and is used in conformance with the Group's
licence. Accordingly, the data in this directory is licensed under the
same licence:

    Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)
    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

This means any redistribution or adaptation of this data must:
  - give attribution to the EDRDG / KANJIDIC project, and
  - be distributed under CC BY-SA 4.0 (or a compatible licence).

Source / attribution:
  - KANJIDIC project: https://www.edrdg.org/wiki/index.php/KANJIDIC_Project
  - EDRDG licence:    https://www.edrdg.org/edrdg/licence.html

Note: this CC BY-SA 4.0 licence applies ONLY to the contents of
public/data/. The application source code is licensed separately under the
Apache License 2.0 (see /LICENSE).
